This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with the problem of recommending items to users based on their side information. It also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing and text mining, which makes it possible to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category. The paper also involves data management and storage, which makes it possible to belong to the Databases (cs.DB) category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of exploiting heterogeneous side information, which makes it possible to belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
